text: The Cebuano people, (Cebuano: "mga Cebuano, Sugbo, Bisaya") are the majority visayan ethnic cultural group in the province of Cebu, The Cebuano people mainly used the Standard Cebuano particularly in Central Visayas are the Boholano, Eastern Negrense, Siquijor and Leyteño, Despite the Davaoeño people are located in Metro Davao.http://www.ethnicgroupsphilippines.com/ethnic- groups-in-the-philippines/cebuano The Masbateño people has a similar to Cebuano people located at Masbate province in Bicol Region.https://dbpedia.org/page/Cebuano_people ==References== Category:Ethnic groups in the Philippines
title: Cebuano people
